<section xmlns:ns0="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <num>20-322</num>
  <heading>When mandatory.</heading>
  <text>A proceeding for standard probate shall be instituted:</text>
  <para>
    <num>(a)</num>
    <text>if, at any time before abbreviated probate,</text>
    <para>
      <num>(1)</num>
      <text>an interested person or creditor makes a request; or</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(2)</num>
      <text>it appears to the Court that the petition for abbreviated probate is materially incomplete or incorrect in any respect; or</text>
    </para>
  </para>
  <para>
    <num>(b)</num>
    <text>in accordance with the provisions of section 20-331.</text>
  </para>
